<hr />
<h2><a name='naming'>Naming Conventions:</a></h2>
<set name='name'><em>Agent</em></set>

<p> An Agent name without a final slash is redirected to the Agent's ``home
    page'' (usually <code>home.xh</code>).  With a final slash you will always
    go to a more-or-less generic index page.  A name of the form <a
    href='/~&AGENT:name;'>/~&name;</a> (i.e. prefixing a tilde to the Agent's
    name) will take you to the Agent's ``home page''.
</p>

<dl>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/'>/~&name;/</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> An alias for the &name; agent's home directory.
  </dd>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/.'>/~&name;/.</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> A generic listing of the agent's home directory.  This will work
       with <em>any</em> directory, not just agent homes, although it can be
       hidden by the site designer.
  </dd>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/DATA/'>/~&name;/DATA/</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> Usually the &name; agent's data directory, if it has one.  This is just
       a convention that may not be universal.
  </dd>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/DATA/.'>/~&name;/.</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> A generic listing of the &name; agent's data directory.
       </dd>
</dl>


